<p><strong>Credit explanation:</strong> 1 AI credit typically = $0.01 in model access at standard API rates. Copilot's "flexible" credits (in Pro+) are the higher-usage pool and represent $70 in API value. Cursor credits are direct API spend; Claude Code subscriptions offer unlimited usage at a fixed monthly cost.</p>

<h2>Entry-Level Options ($10–$20/month)</h2>

<div class="comparison-card">
  <h3>GitHub Copilot Pro ($10/month)</h3>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Individual developers, part-time coding, learning.</p>
  <p><strong>Includes:</strong> 1,500 AI credits/month ($15 value), basic models, code completion.</p>
  <p><strong>Cost per day:</strong> $0.33 (roughly 50 AI credits/day if evenly used).</p>
  <p><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Lowest price but smallest credit pool. Runs out fast for heavy users.</p>
</div>

<div class="comparison-card">
  <h3>Cursor Pro ($20/month)</h3>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Full-time developers, independent contractors.</p>
  <p><strong>Includes:</strong> $20 API credits/month, Claude 3.5 Sonnet access, chat + inline editing.</p>
  <p><strong>Cost per day:</strong> $0.67 (roughly $0.67 per day in model API).</p>
  <p><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Fixed credit budget; overage charges if you exceed $20. However, Cursor's interface provides high token efficiency compared to raw API use.</p>
</div>

<div class="comparison-card">
  <h3>Claude Code Pro ($20/month)</h3>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Full-time developers who want unlimited usage.</p>
  <p><strong>Includes:</strong> Unlimited Claude API access at standard rates, caching support, batch API use.</p>
  <p><strong>Cost per day:</strong> $0.67 (fixed cost regardless of usage).</p>
  <p><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Unlimited usage means no surprise charges. If you use more than ~$0.67/day equivalent, Claude Code can be more cost-effective than Cursor's fixed credits.</p>
</div>

<h2>Mid-Tier Options ($39–$100/month)</h2>

<div class="comparison-card">
  <h3>GitHub Copilot Pro+ ($39/month)</h3>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Teams using GitHub integrations, enterprise deployment.</p>
  <p><strong>Includes:</strong> 7,000 AI credits/month ($70 value at standard rates), advanced models, priority support.</p>
  <p><strong>Cost per day:</strong> $1.30 (~230 AI credits/day if evenly used).</p>
  <p><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Credit-based model requires monitoring. If your team consistently uses more than 7,000 credits, overflow charges apply.</p>
</div>

<div class="comparison-card">
  <h3>Cursor Pro+ ($60/month)</h3>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> High-volume freelancers, small teams (3–5 developers).</p>
  <p><strong>Includes:</strong> $60 API credits/month, unlimited chat, advanced models, priority queue.</p>
  <p><strong>Cost per day:</strong> $2.00 (roughly $2/day in API credits).</p>
  <p><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Higher per-person cost but 3x the monthly credit budget. Good for teams where some members use heavily, others lightly.</p>
</div>

<div class="comparison-card">
  <h3>Claude Code Max 5x ($100/month)</h3>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Teams of 2–3 developers sharing one subscription.</p>
  <p><strong>Includes:</strong> 5x Claude API usage cap (raises rate limits), unlimited access, priority support.</p>
  <p><strong>Cost per day:</strong> $3.33 (fixed cost; no per-token limit).</p>
  <p><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Unlimited usage simplifies billing. Most beneficial if your actual API spend would exceed $100/month at standard rates.</p>
</div>

<h2>Premium Options ($100–$200/month)</h2>

<div class="comparison-card">
  <h3>GitHub Copilot Max ($100/month)</h3>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Enterprise teams, high-volume departments.</p>
  <p><strong>Includes:</strong> 20,000 AI credits/month ($200 value), all advanced models, GPT-5.5 turbo access, dedicated support.</p>
  <p><strong>Cost per day:</strong> $3.33 (~660 AI credits/day if evenly used).</p>
  <p><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Highest credit pool but credit-based pricing requires management. Best for organizations with predictable usage patterns.</p>
</div>

<div class="comparison-card">
  <h3>Cursor Ultra ($200/month)</h3>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Large teams (10+), agencies, heavy compute workloads.</p>
  <p><strong>Includes:</strong> $200 API credits/month, all models, unlimited chat windows, priority support.</p>
  <p><strong>Cost per day:</strong> $6.67 (roughly $6.67/day in API credits).</p>
  <p><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Highest tier. Cursor's interface efficiency means $200 in credits often goes further than raw API usage would.</p>
</div>

<div class="comparison-card">
  <h3>Claude Code Max 20x ($200/month)</h3>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Teams of 5–10 developers or very high-volume solo practitioners.</p>
  <p><strong>Includes:</strong> 20x Claude API usage multiplier, unlimited access, batch API, extended context windows.</p>
  <p><strong>Cost per day:</strong> $6.67 (fixed cost regardless of usage).</p>
  <p><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Highest price tier, but unlimited means no surprise charges. Best ROI if actual API spend would exceed $200/month.</p>
</div>

<h2>Cost Optimization Considerations</h2>

<p><strong>1. Usage patterns matter:</strong> If your actual LLM API consumption is $500/month, Claude Code Max 20x ($200) saves you $300/month vs. raw API. But if it's $50/month, Cursor Pro ($20) is better.</p>

<p><strong>2. Credit efficiency:</strong> Copilot's credit model is transparent: 1 credit = $0.01 of API value. But you only see credits consumed, not the underlying token usage. Cursor and Claude Code show per-interaction costs more clearly.</p>

<p><strong>3. Model access:</strong> Copilot Pro+ is the only plan offering access to GPT-5.5 turbo at this price point. Cursor Pro and Claude Code Pro use Claude Sonnet / Opus, which differ in speed and cost. Choose based on coding task complexity.</p>

<p><strong>4. Team scaling:</strong> For 5+ developers, compare total cost:</p>

<ul>
  <li>5× Copilot Pro = $50/month ($0.30 total cost-per-user-per-day)</li>
  <li>5× Cursor Pro = $100/month ($0.67 total cost-per-user-per-day)</li>
  <li>1× Claude Code Max 20x (shared) = $200/month ($1.33 per user if split equally)</li>
  <li>GitHub Copilot Enterprise (org license) = $21/seat/month = $105 for 5 users</li>
</ul>

<p>For 5 developers, Copilot Pro at scale ($50) beats all others. For 10+ developers, Copilot Enterprise ($21/seat) becomes competitive.</p>

<h2>How to Choose</h2>

<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>Solo developer? Pick by daily usage.</h3>
  <p>If you code 4 hours/day: Cursor Pro or Claude Code Pro ($20/month). If 2 hours/day: Copilot Pro ($10/month) is fine.</p>
</div>

<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>Small team (2–5 people)?</h3>
  <p>Sum individual usage. If total is $50–$100/month (raw API equivalent), Cursor Pro+ ($60) shared across 2–3 people is most economical. If $100+/month, Claude Code Max 5x ($100) for the team saves per-person cost.</p>
</div>

<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>Large team (10+)?</h3>
  <p>Use GitHub Copilot Enterprise ($21/seat/month) for org-wide governance, or negotiate bulk pricing with Cursor or Anthropic.</p>
</div>

<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>Cost-first decision?</h3>
  <p>If your actual LLM API spend (raw tokens) exceeds your subscription cost, unlimited tiers (Claude Code) are better. If your usage is light, credit-based tiers (Copilot, Cursor) let you pay only for what you use.</p>
</div>

